{"article_id":"mdNwKFllbG9ClTyo","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The unemployment rate ticked up to 8.3 percent in July ,","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"reflecting a stagnant economic picture","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"as hiring improved","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"but not by enough","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"to make a dent in the sea of unemployed Americans .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"The Labor Department report , in a glimmer of positive news after three straight months of dismal jobs numbers , showed","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"that hiring reached its best level since February ,","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"with 163,000 jobs added .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"But the number brings the economy back to treading-water status .","depth":4},{"id":9,"text":"The economy added an average of 151,000 jobs a month this year , roughly the same as last year 's pace .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"That 's not enough","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"to satisfy the 12.8 million Americans","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"who are unemployed .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"It would take 250,000 new jobs a month","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"to rapidly bring the unemployment rate down .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"With the rate rising from 8.2 percent to 8.3 percent ,","depth":4},{"id":16,"text":"Republicans amped up their criticism of President Obama 's stewardship Friday .","depth":4},{"id":17,"text":"`` Today 's increase in the unemployment rate is a hammer blow to struggling middle-class families , ''","depth":5},{"id":18,"text":"Mitt Romney said in a statement .","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"Speaking later in North Las Vegas ,","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"he called the sustained high unemployment an `` extraordinary record of failure . ''","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"`` That 's the longest period of time , 42 months ...","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"we 've had unemployment above 8 percent in American history , ''","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"Romney said .","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"Both sides are to using the report","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"to double down on their respective tax plans .","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"House Speaker John Boehner said","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"`` any new job creation is welcome news , ''","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"but that unemployment above 8 percent makes it `` insane to raise taxes on small businesses . ''","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"Republicans want to extend the Bush-era tax rates for all Americans ;","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"Obama and congressional Democrats largely want to extend them for those","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"making less than $ 250,000 ,","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"letting rates rise for top earners .","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"Obama ,","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"speaking just minutes after Romney ,","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"said Friday","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"that raising taxes on the middle class is `` the last thing","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"that we should be doing . ''","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"He noted","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"that the jobs report means","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"the economy has created 4.5 million new jobs in the last 29 months , and 1.1 million this year .","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"`` But let 's acknowledge","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"we 've still got too many folks out there","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"who are looking for work , ''","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"Obama said .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"House Democratic Leader Nancy Pelosi touted the fact","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"that July marked the 29th straight month of private sector job growth .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"`` Last month , 163,000 jobs were created","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"despite Republicans ' refusal","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"to work with President Obama and Democrats","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"to create jobs ,","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"grow our economy ,","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"and ensure the economic security of our middle class , ''","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"she said .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"`` With too many Americans still out of work , the message remains clear :","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"we must do more . ''","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"The government uses two surveys","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"to measure employment .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"A survey of businesses showed job gains .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"The unemployment rate comes from a survey of households ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"which showed","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"fewer people had jobs .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"Economists say","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"the business survey is more reliable .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"Investors appeared pleased with the report .","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"Futures","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"tracking the Standard & Poor 's 500 index and the Dow Jones industrial average","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"gained about 1 percent .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"The stock market is coming off four days of losses .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"Yields on government bonds also rose","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"after the report came out","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"as investors moved money out of low-risk assets .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"A better outlook on hiring could prompt the Federal Reserve to hold off taking more action","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"to spur growth .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"The U.S. central bank ,","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"which ended a two-day policy meeting Wednesday ,","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"signaled in a statement a growing inclination","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"to take further steps","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"if hiring does n't pick up .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"The job gains were broad-based .","depth":5},{"id":80,"text":"Manufacturing added 25,000 jobs , the most since March .","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"Restaurants and bars added 29,000 .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"Retailers hired 7,000 more workers .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"Education and health services gained 38,000 .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"Governments cut 9,000 positions .","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"Average hourly wages also increased by 2 cents .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"Over the past year , wages have increased 1.7 percent","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"-- matching the rate of inflation .","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"Despite July 's job gains ,","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"the economy remains weak","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"more than three years after economists declared","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"the recession had ended in June 2009 .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"Growth slowed to an annual rate of 1.5 percent in the April-June quarter , down from 2 percent in the first quarter and 4.1 percent in the final three months of 2011 .","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"Manufacturing activity shrank for the second straight month in July ,","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"a private survey said Wednesday .","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"Consumer confidence improved slightly last month","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"but remains weak .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"Rising pessimism about the future is taking a toll on businesses and consumers ,","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"many economists say .","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"Europe 's financial crisis has weakened that region 's economy ,","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"hurting U.S. exports .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"Worries have also intensified","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"that the U.S. economy will fall off a `` fiscal cliff '' at the end of the year .","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"That 's when tax increases and deep spending cuts will take effect","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"unless Congress reaches a budget deal .","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"A recession could follow ,","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"Fed Chairman Ben Bernanke has warned .","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"Americans are responding","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"by spending less","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"and saving more .","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"A big reason","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"growth slowed in the second quarter","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"was that consumer spending ,","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"which accounts for roughly 70 percent of economic activity ,","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"slowed to an annual growth rate of 1.5 percent .","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"That was down from 2.4 percent in the first quarter .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":231,"left":130,"right":230,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":120,"right":129,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":0,"right":119,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":1,"right":118,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":2,"right":117,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":117,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":122,"right":128,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":122,"left":5,"right":121,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":121,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":8,"right":127,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":125,"right":126,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":125,"left":9,"right":124,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":124,"left":10,"right":123,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":230,"left":138,"right":229,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":131,"right":137,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":137,"left":132,"right":136,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent"